paragraph_US: pO2 (Partial Pressure of Oxygen) reflects the amount of oxygen gas dissolved in the blood.
paragraph_SI: pO2 (Partial Pressure of Oxygen) reflects the amount of oxygen gas dissolved in the blood.

paragraph_US: It primarily measures the effectiveness of the lungs in pulling oxygen into the blood stream from the atmosphere.
paragraph_SI: It primarily measures the effectiveness of the lungs in pulling oxygen into the blood stream from the atmosphere.

paragraph_US: Elevated pO2 levels are associated with:  Increased oxygen levels in the inhaled air or polycythemia
paragraph_SI: Elevated pO2 levels are associated with:  Increased oxygen levels in the inhaled air or polycythemia
